claim.claim-text:
1. A method for distributing digital video data between one or more video service providers, the method comprising:
receiving, at one or more computer systems associated with a first video service provider, first digital data comprising a first plurality of digital images at a first image resolution, wherein each digital image in the first plurality of digital images in the first digital data is encoded in a first color space, wherein the first color space is configured for playback on film video equipment;
generating, with one or more processors associated with the one or more computer systems associated with the first video service provider, second digital data comprising a second plurality of digital images at the first image resolution in response to the first plurality of digital images in the first digital data and in response to color grading input data, wherein each digital image in the second plurality of digital images in the second digital data is color-graded and encoded in a second color space according to the color grading input data, wherein the second color space is configured for video that utilizes consumer High Definition (HD) video equipment;
distributing an encoded image data package that includes the second plurality of digital images in the second digital data compressed with a compression encoding substantially independent of integer pixel translation of the second plurality of digital images
between the first video service provider and one or more second video service providers; and
generating, with one or more processors associated with one or more computer systems associated with the one or more second video service providers, third digital data comprising a third plurality of digital images at a second image resolution in response to the encoded image data package and an encoding pipeline associated with the one or more second video service providers configured to at least resize the second digital data to the second image resolution for the consumer HD video equipment, wherein the first image resolution is different from the second image resolution.

10. A non-transitory computer-readable medium storing computer-executable code for distributing digital video data between one or more video service providers, the non-transitory computer-readable medium comprising:
code for receiving first digital data comprising a first plurality of digital images at a first image resolution, wherein each digital image in the first plurality of digital images in the first digital data is encoded in a first color space, wherein the first color space is configured for video that utilizes film video equipment;
code for generating second digital data comprising a second plurality of digital images at the first resolution in response to the first plurality of digital images in the first digital data and in response to color grading input data, wherein each digital image in the second plurality of digital images in the second digital data is color-graded and encoded in a second color space according to the color grading input data, wherein the second color space is configured for video that utilizes consumer High Definition (HD) video equipment;
code communicating an encoded image data package that includes the second plurality of digital images in the second digital data compressed with a compression encoding substantially independent of integer pixel translation of the second plurality of digital images to one or more computer systems of one or more video service providers that generate third digital data comprising a third plurality of digital images at a second image resolution in response to the encoded image data package and an encoding pipeline associated with the one or more video service providers configured to at least resize the second digital data to the second image resolution for the consumer HD video equipment, wherein the first image resolution is different from the second image resolution.

18. A method for distributing digital video data, the method comprising:
receiving, at one or more computer systems, digital data that is encoded as a first digital master configured for theatrical use, the first digital master including one or more digital images in a first color space and having a first resolution, wherein the first color space and the first resolution are defined according to aspects of theatrical use video equipment;
receiving, at the one or more computer systems, a specification of at least one target digital media device format, wherein a target color space associated with consumer High Definition (HD) video devices is a color space associated with the at least one target digital media device format;
packaging, with one or more processors associated with the one or more computer systems, second digital data generated from the one or more digital images in the first digital data into an encoded package based on the specification, wherein the second digital data includes one or more digital images having at least a second resolution with reduced pixel artifacts that is equal to or less than the first image resolution and greater than a third resolution associated with the specification of the at least one target digital media device format, wherein the second digital data is compressed with a compression encoding substantially independent of integer pixel translation of the one or more digital images of the first digital data; and
distributing the encoded package to one or more video service providers such that the one or more video service providers directly encode from the second digital data to third digital data in at least the target color space and at the third resolution based on at least one transfer curve of the at least one target digital media device format.
